cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the development of a convolutional neural network for automated nuclear segmentation and classification in histology images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of instance-rich information and distances to centres of mass suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. Additionally, the application of the method to multiple tissue types and the introduction of a new dataset suggests a potential focus on multimedia (cs.MM) applications.
